## BookTube Community and Dune Reviews

BookTube is a subcommunity on YouTube that focuses on books and literature. The BookTube community has, to date, reached hundreds of thousands of viewers worldwide. While the majority of BookTubers focus on Young Adult literature, many address other genres, including science fiction like Frank Herbert's Dune.

## Popular BookTube Channels Covering Dune

Several prominent BookTube channels have reviewed Dune:

**Daniel Greene** is a creator who covers a huge range of fantasy and sci-fi titles — and he truly caters to all sorts of readers. Maybe you enjoy niche Tolkien or Brandon Sanderson humor, or maybe you want to read Stephen King but don't know where to start. Wherever you lie on the spectrum, Greene makes creative and knowledgeable videos that vary in levels of previous experience required.(no content)He's known for Book Reviews, Science Fiction Deep Dives (Dune, Foundation, etc), TV Show Discussions/Reviews.

(ClauReadsBooks), Dakota Warren (Dakota Warren), Carley Thorne (uncarley), Jesse George (Jesse the Reader), and Daniel Greene (Daniel Greene).

## Video Essay Channels

Beyond traditional BookTube, there are channels that create in-depth video essays about Dune:

**Alt Shift X** has also created Dune content, with ASX Dune video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R0krUthYxF4.

## Community Size and Engagement

The BookTuber with the most viewers boasts over 410,000 subscribers. The BookTube community has grown significantly, with many channels having thousands (and sometimes hundreds of thousands) of subscribers. BookTube channels exist globally in English, Portuguese, Italian, French, and Spanish, among other languages.
